&lt;p style="margin-left:-9.0pt;"&gt;Carole Levitt, founder/principal of Internet For Lawyers (IFL), is an internationally recognized CLE seminar speaker and best-selling American Bar Association author. She writes and speaks on Internet investigative and legal research, social media research, social media ethics, and technology for lawyers. &amp;nbsp;Since 1999, IFL has provided law firms, corporations, and local and state Bar Associations around the country with professional and entertaining turn-key CLE programs. The company focuses on delivering information about free investigative and background research resources available on the Internet.&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
&lt;p style="margin-left:-9.0pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
&lt;p style="margin-left:-9.0pt;"&gt;Together with co-author Mark Rosch, Levitt has written several ABA Law Practice Division books, including &amp;quot;Google Gmail and Calendar For Lawyers in One Hour&amp;quot; (2013), two editions of &amp;quot;The Lawyer&amp;rsquo;s Guide to Fact Finding on the Internet,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;Google For Lawyers,&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Find Info Like a Pro,&amp;quot; Volumes 1 and 2. They have also just completed the thirteenth edition of their book &amp;quot;The Cybersleuth&amp;#39;s Guide to the Internet&amp;quot; (2015, IFL Press). Levitt also co-authored &amp;ldquo;Internet Legal Research on a Budget (ABA, 2013) with Judy K. Davis.&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
&lt;p style="margin-left:-9.0pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
&lt;p style="margin-left:-9.0pt;"&gt;Previously, Levitt was a California attorney, a law librarian in Chicago and Los Angeles, and a Legal Research and Writing Professor at Pepperdine University School of Law. She graduated with distinction from The John Marshall Law School in Chicago and was a member of the school&amp;rsquo;s law review. Carole has a Masters in Library Science and a B.A. in Political Science from the University of Illinois.&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
&lt;p style="margin-left:-9.0pt;"&gt;She is active in numerous professional associations, including the American Bar Association (ABA) and the Association of Continuing Legal Education (ACLEA).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mark Rosch is Vice-President of Internet for Lawyers and President of its CLEseminars.com division. He&amp;rsquo;s an internationally recognized speaker and author on the subjects of using the Internet for investigative and background research, Google search, and Google Cloud Apps.&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
&#x0D;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
&#x0D;
&lt;p&gt;He has co-authored numerous books and hundreds of articles on these and other related topics, receiving top industry recognition for his work.&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
&#x0D;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
&#x0D;
&lt;p&gt;Mark is a Fellow in the College of Law Practice Management, an honorary society that honors and recognizes distinguished law practice management professionals, and in 2013 he was named to the &amp;quot;Fastcase Fifty,&amp;quot; recognizing &amp;ldquo;50 of the smartest, most courageous innovators, techies, visionaries, and leaders in the law.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
&#x0D;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
&#x0D;
&lt;p&gt;Mark is a long-time member of ACLEA and the ABA and is active member in both organizations. He has served in numerous leadership positions &amp;ndash; recently completing a 3-year term on the ABA TECHSHOW Planning Board.&lt;/p&gt;&#x0D;
